  "prompt": "Where/How can I get Section 8 housing quickly, if I'm on SSI/SSDI?",
  "response": "Here are some steps to get Section 8 housing quickly while on SSI/SSDI:\n\n1. Contact local resources:\n- Public Housing Authority (PHA) in your city/county\n- Local HUD office\n- Social services department\n\n2. Steps to apply:\n- Get on waiting lists immediately (many have long wait times)\n- Apply to multiple housing authorities\n- Request \"priority status\" due to disability\n- Provide all SSI/SSDI documentation\n- Check if your area has any emergency housing programs\n\n3. Additional resources:\n- Local disability services organizations\n- Social workers\n- 211 information hotline\n- Online housing assistance websites\n- Community action agencies\n\n4. Online application options:\n- HUD's website\n- Your state/local housing authority websites\n- Affordable housing websites\n\n5. Helpful tips:\n- Be persistent\n- Follow up regularly\n- Keep all documentation current\n- Consider shared housing or group living options\n- Check for subsidized housing complexes\n\nSome areas have faster processing for disabled individuals, so emphasize your SSI/SSDI status when applying.\n\nFor the most accurate, location-specific information, contact your local housing authority directly.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these points?",
